"a criminal failure to render assistance to people in danger. Integration between preventive and curative measures is technically necessary and politically desirable. The value of curative care is unquestionable. Nonetheless, curative measures are merely a palliative for the medical problems most frequently encountered in disaster situations. They improve individual cases to some extent, but do not provide reasonable solutions in the medium term. A purely curative approach leads to a vicious circle which is difficult to break. If priority is given to the problem of lack of food, by facilitating access to food resources or directly providing victims with the food that they need, not only will the prevalence of malnutrition decrease, but also that of the medical problems that are generally closely linked to it."